  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Slice the<strong> flat white mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Deseed the <strong>sweet pointed pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1603112117342-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1603112117342-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1603112117342-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1603112117342-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1603112117342-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> and <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the pepper is beginning to char – this is your <strong>roasted pepper & mushrooms</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
